rComments: Professor Chamberlin is an awesome professor. He clearly knows a lot and is so friendly and understanding. I've never met a more approachable or friendly professor. In the seminar he didn't talk as much as I wished he would, and he left the class to our discussion and presentations, which was sort of a shame -- I wish we could have had both.

Ted was my first English prof at U of T nearly 40 years ago.  He was, and still is, a lovely and amazing man -- learned, modest, funny and insightful. He was a great influence on me, inspriring and encouraging my study of literature.

he's so extremely knowlegable!  I enjoyed the structure of the class :mostly discussion, but I wish he would have said more. It's nice to see him enjoying the students' comments though. He's very encouraging.

AMAZING PROFESSOR! Probably the single greatest in my U of T experience. Knows so much about all genres of literature, and brings this into his discussions, so you are learning about everything. Amazing speaker, great sense of humour, creative assignments that are marked fairly, interesting and illuminating discussions in every class.

An amazing and inspiring prof.  One of the best english courses I have ever taken.  certainly my fave english seminar.  he brought so much life to canadian poetry. very spiritual...and i think it is so cool that he published an essay called "Ganja in Jamaica"!!
